{"updated_at": "2011-11-17T22:17:46Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2011-11-17T22:17:46Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2782914", "id": 2782914, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3664", "issue_id": 3664, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fxn/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/fxn", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fxn/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fxn/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fxn/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "7223c62b7310e164eb79c740188abbda", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fxn/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/fxn", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fxn/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/7223c62b7310e164eb79c740188abbda?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F4a11654ad1e1e48352252859ff3032a0.png", "id": 3387, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fxn/events{/privacy}", "login": "fxn", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fxn/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fxn/followers"}, "body": "The link_to example above is just one example. Interpolation in _html translation strings does not escape, and people rely on that. It can be a link_to call, or an arbitrary string.\r\n\r\nWe think the behavior after applying this patch would be more coherent with the overall way safe strings work. But it is going to break applications of people that are relying on the way the code works, it is unclear that this has to be treated as a security fix.\r\n\r\nSo by now we have patched the docs (d57d809), and perhaps revisit this for 3.2.", "_id": {"$oid": "523833c6bd3543c15100fa77"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3664#issuecomment-2782914"}
